why can t i receive email from certain sites while email from other sites works fine stanford answers stanford university stanford answers why can t i receive email from certain sites while email from other sites works fine categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home why can t i receive email from certain sites while email from other sites works fine search this site the incoming email was identified as spam by stanford's anti spam filtering system the stanford email servers have some rules to block out spam by default all email tagged as definite spam coming into stanford is automatically deleted at the email gateways email is blocked usually due to one of the following reasons the sender address is invalid if the domain of the sender address does not resolve in dns the email is rejected the sending site is using an invalid helo command the internet protocol for email exchanges specify that arguments for the helo command contain the fully qualified domain name of the sending site if the helo command does not contain a valid domain name the email is rejected for more information see section 4.1 1.1 of the simple mail transfer protocol standard the ip address of the sending site does not resolve the ip address of the sending site must resolve to a valid dns hostname email viruses and spam stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
